Description:
C# statement/expression interpreter
Tie is dynamic language which accepts C# statement/expression syntax and javascript like function and class syntax. 
Include lexical analysis, parser and virtual machine(VM), support script debug, breakpoint.
Middleware, high performance, compact size around 150KB(tie.dll)

Execute C# statements and expressions, call any classes/methods of .net DLL 
Build Tie script event handler, delegate, function and class as well, which can be invoked by .NET.

Support  WinForm, WPF, Sliverlight, ASP.NET, JSON
Support .NET 2.0/3.0/3.5/4.0
Support Generic class, Extension method, Lambda expression, serialize any objects, high level programming 
Support 3rd party software such as DevExpress, Telerik

Example1:
   Memory ds = new Memory();
   ds.AddObject("a", 10);
   Script.Execute("if(a>1) {a=a+1; b=true; }", ds);
   // (int)ds["a"] --> 11;
   // (bool)ds["b"] --> true;

Example2:
  //suppose there are  button "button1" and TextBox "textBox1" in WinForm
   Script script = new Script();
   script.DS = new Memory();
   script.DS.AddObject("btn", button1);
   script.DS.AddObject("txt", textBox1);
   string code= @"
     txt.Text = ""No"";
     btn.Click+=delegate(sender,e)
     {
         txt.Text =""Yes"";
     };
    ";
    script.Execute(code);
    //textBox1.Text --> "Yes" when button1 is clicked.
   ";
